premise_source_doc_sentence: It has U.S. Food and Drug Administration approval to treat major depression , which it received in 1998 , and is prescribed off-label for other conditions .

It is approved by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration  (  FDA  )  for the treatment of adults and children over 12 years of age with major depressive disorder  (  MDD  )  or generalized anxiety disorder  (  GAD  )  .

Like citalopram and escitalopram , didesmethyl  (  es  )  citalopram functions as a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor  (  SSRI  )  , and is responsible for some of its parents ' therapeutic benefits .
Like citalopram and escitalopram , desmethylcitalopram functions as a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor  (  SSRI  )  , and is responsible for some of its parents ' therapeutic benefits .
Currently only escitalopram , the S stereoisomer of the SSRI citalopram is included in this category .
